Sentencas: Ni/YSZ cermet anode is required to satisfy various properties as a key component of anode-supported type SOFC, since the cell performance is dependent upon anode properties.
Titulo: Effect of compaction pressure on the microstructure evolution of anode substrate for SOFC application

Sentencas: Ni/YSZ anode, with complicated structural features, consists of three different phases such as metallic Ni, YSZ ceramic and pores.
Titulo: Effect of compaction pressure on the microstructure evolution of anode substrate for SOFC application

Sentencas: The correlation between those structural features makes it difficult to independently optimize individual function of anode such as gas permeability, electrical conductivity and electrochemical activity.
Titulo: Effect of compaction pressure on the microstructure evolution of anode substrate for SOFC application

Sentencas: Microstructure of anode substrate was evaluated in terms of pore structure and metallic phase development by varying compaction pressure.
Titulo: Effect of compaction pressure on the microstructure evolution of anode substrate for SOFC application

Sentencas: The resulting pore structure went through a gradual transition, which was correspondingly reflected in gas permeability and electrical conductivity of anode substrate.
Titulo: Effect of compaction pressure on the microstructure evolution of anode substrate for SOFC application

Sentencas: An effort to establish structure-property-processing correlation has been made in this study to achieve improved anode performance.
Titulo: Effect of compaction pressure on the microstructure evolution of anode substrate for SOFC application
